ce:section.ce:para:
Furthermore, for elements having a specific heat per unit area of more than 20 kJ/(m2. K), the analysis shall be carried out over a period which is an integer multiple of 24 h. Only when the following requirements are met, the test could be ended.

                                 1

The test lasts longer than 72 h (3days);


                                 2

The R-value obtained at the end of the test does not deviate by more than ± 5 % from the value obtained 24 h prior by more than ± 5 %;


                                 3

There is no deviation of more than ± 5 % between the R-value derived from the data of the final time period of the same duration and the values derived from the data of the first time period during INT (2 x DT/3) days of the measurement period. Where DT is the test's duration in days; INT is the integer part;


                                 4

One of the techniques outlined in the standard should be applied if the change in heat stored in the wall exceeds 5 % of the heat flowing through the wall during the test period.
